(edit, 9 years later... hello smart contract developers, I know that's why you're here lol) What is the fastest algorithm for finding the square root of a number? I created one that can find the square root of " $987654321$ " to $16$ decimal places in just $20$ iterations I've now tried Newton's method as well as my own method (Newtons code as seen below) What is the fastest known algorithm for taking the second root of a number? My code for Newton's Method (*Edit: there was an error in my code, it is fixed in the comments below): a=2   //2nd root
    b=97654321   //base
    n=1   //initial guess
    c=0   //current iteration (this is a changing variable)
    r=500000   //total number of iterations to run
    while (c<r) 
    {
        m = n-(((n^a)-b)/(a*b))  //Newton's algorithm
        n=m
        c++;
        trace(m + "  <--guess   ...   iteration-->  " + c)
    }
